 Dhaka, May 2 (bdnews24.com)RAB on Sunday recovered Tk 28 lakh of HSBC Bank's Tk 45 lakh stolen by a driver of a security firm and arrested three for alleged ties. G4S, a firm that provides security service to the bank, on Apr 22 reported that one of their staff had run away with Tk 45 lakh from a microbus used to carry money. Microbus driver Farid Ali's son's girlfriend Sania Islam Sumi, 21, her mother Manwara Begum, 40, and her friend Mamun Siraj, 24 were arrested on a tip-off at a house of Kuril. However, the elite force is still looking for Farid and his son Shah Alam, RAB deputy director (law and media section) Major Iftekhar Ahmed told bdnews24.com. He told bdnews24.com that Farid had disappeared from the capital's Motijheel business district with the money. A case was filed with the Motijheel police. On Apr 22, HSBC Bank drew Tk 5 crore from Bangladesh Bank in Motijheel and G4S, responsible for the security of the bank, carried the money to HSBC branch. When the HSBC's employees were moving the loaded trunks from the microbus to the bank volt, Farid allegedly escaped a good chunk. bd
